the beginning but as it turns out it is not. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0"=
>Claude Opus 4.8 was used to audit Zcash's code. It uncovered a critical vu=
lnerability in the Orchard shielded pool (Zcash's privacy tech, live since =
2022). The bug could have let attackers mint unlimited counterfeit ZEC insi=
de the shielded pool=E2=80=94essentially an "infinite money glitch" that wo=
uld have been undetectable due to Zcash's strong privacy features. It stemm=
ed from insufficient verification in the circuit.</p><p style=3D"margin:10p=
x 0">What actually happened:</p><ul><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Zcash de=
vs responded fast.</p></li><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Soft fork on June=
 2 disabled Orchard transactions.</p></li><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Ha=
rd fork (NU6.2) on the same day patched it.</p></li></ul><h2>NOTE I AM NOT =
SAYING ZEC IS DEAD BUT I AM HIGHLIGHTING THE RISKS and for the record I nev=
er bought into ZEC despite lots of pressure. </h2><p style=3D"margin:10px 0=
">It also shows how narrative is controlling price now... and for weeks on =
